status_message:
Hindi ko inexpect that a simple yes or no question would grow this big. My post with a photo of the "mochangtanga" pamphlet is meant  for verification and clarification; and not intended to judge the school which is why I ask them through my post and did not react prematurely. 

Mahirap kasi na magreact ako agad and then malalaman ko na hindi naman pala sa kanila galing yan, thus, I raised the question if it was true or not. At least now, through questioning in my post and their posted answers, we know that this pamphlet does NOT represent (I hope) the Ateneo de Manila University as a whole but just that of one of their school organization. If it is one of your way in tackling the issues in social media then I am supporting it regardless of its negative impact towards me. I just hope that if this school organization of Ateneo de manila has time to spare and create a satire using my blog as the center, I hope they can also tackle ang pagiging biased ng ilang news outlets and use as well ang ibang anonymous blogs/pages who are really spreading fake news/article. Hiling ko po ay sana hindi lamang po nakafocus ang attention sa mga Duterte supporters kung talagang nais niyong talakayin ang problema sa social media. Sana po ay maging patas at talakayin maging ang mga anti-Duterte pages para hindi po magmukha na mayroon kayong kinikilingan, para hindi naman po magmukha na ang buong Ateneo de manila university ay against the President, kasi marami po ako kakilala na atenista but also a fellow Duterte supporter.

PAANO BA NAGING BIASED ANG ILANG MEDIA?

If you are a frequent listener, viewer, or reader of news reports you will see the abundance of news reports of criticisms on how the current president speak, the issue about Extra Judicial Killing, the supposed David vs Goliath battle between Sen. De Lima and Pres.  Duterte, how the President made the wrong call with regards to foreign policy, interviews on the family of the victims of EJK, and so on and so forth. In short, the news reports nowadays are filled with the negative views on the current administration. Which is why a lot of people can be misled that the current administration is not doing anything good at all. While I admit that reports about the positive impact and actions of the current administration are also going around, you must also admit that it is not balanced. Maraming nagawa ang kasalukuyang administrasyon in just 100 days, pero ang mga balita ay napupuno ng paulit-ulit na pagbabalita sa mga negative side lamang.

Isa sa mga Propaganda ng mga Dilaw ay gumawa ng mga fake "Duterte Blog" tapos maglalabas ng mga fake news para ito ay i-share ng mga DDS (Pro-Duterte). At pag ito ay kinagat ng mga Pro-Duterte biglang sasabihin ng mga DILAW na BOBO, TANGA or DUTERTARDS ang mga ito. Kaya mga kaDDS ingat po tayo sa mga blog na ito.

ARE THEY REALLY CREDIBLE?

Let's admit this: Madali tayong maniwala sa mga balita. We don't think twice to believe what is being presented to us especially if it's presented to us by experts in their field. We believe the news reports because we know that it was created by a group of capable researchers, back it up with a knowledgeable reporter and a trusted news network site; this, I believe, is the perfect ingredient for being a credible news outlet. There was a time when I respect all these news outlets because they do their jobs, they report everything whether it is positive or negative, whether it is trending or not, whether people will hate them for it or not. But nowadays, I can just count in my hand the news outlet I can trust.

Yung iba hindi man nila sinasabi ng direkta, mararamdaman mo ito sa kanilang pananalita. Kasi nga po karamihan (hindi lahat) sa MAINSTREAM MEDIA ay talagang may direktang utos mula sa may-ari ng kanilang pahayagan o network na siraan ang gobyernong DUTERTE. Kaya ang idinidiin nila ay ang maliliit na pagkukulang sa bawat departamento. Halimbawa nalang diyan ay sa dami ng magagandang ginawa ng DOTr ano pa ang idiniin ng Maintream Media? Ang issue ng "state of mind" lang daw ang traffic (naipaliwanag na natin ito dati (http://ow.ly/BJJ63054Z9Q). Isa po sa napakasipag na gabinete ng ating pangulo ay si Sec. Manny Pinol. Ngunit minsan mo lang siya mababasa o mapapanuod sa Mainstream Media. Bakit? Hindi kasi ito makulay na balita at hindi ito makakasira kay Pangulong Duterte.  Kaya isa sa dahilan kung bakit ko po tayo nagpupursigi na ma-interview ang mga opisyal ng gobyerno ay dahil hindi ipinapakita ang mga mabubuti nilang ginagawa. TAO DIN PO SILA. They need to be encouraged. Kung ibang media naman hindi na nga ibinabalita ang mga pagbabago ng ahensiya ng gobyerno ay sisiraan pa nila. Kung nagbabalita lamang sana ng pantas ang media ay nalalaman sana ng mamamayang Pilipino at buong mundo ang mga accomplishments ng bawat ahensiya ng ating gobyerno. 100 Days pa lamang ang DUTERTE ADMINISTRATION ngunit nalamapasan na ito ang mga nagawa nakaraang administrasyon sa loob ng 6 na taon.  At isa pa ang masama dito pagbibintangan pa ng "CREDIT GRABBING". Maraming proyekto ang sinimulan ni Aquino ngunit laging hindi natatapos. Bakit kanyo? Kasi ganito yan, sa bawat proyektong pinapasok sa gobyerno marami sa opisyal ay may commission o may kita pag ito ay naapruban. Minsan pa nga napakalaki ng quotation pero pagdating sa implementasyon ay yung mga mabababang klase na ang binibili para yung matira ay binubulsa nalang. Yan ang nangyari sa MRT natin kaya sira lagi. Ngayon pagpasok ng Duterte Administration sa kalagitnaan ng taon halos ubos na ang nakalaang budget na dapat ay para sa buong taon. Kaya todo kayod ang mga gabinete upang maramdaman ng mga tao ang pagbabago dahil yan ay ang utos ng ating Pangulo. Sabay ang MEDIA kesa na ibalita ang mga pagbabago ay yung mga mapanlinlang na mga issue pa ang ibabalita? Tapos magagalit sila pag sila'y sinasabihang UNFAIR or BIASED! Kaya pag may nagsasabi sa akin na imposible daw na wala akong bayad sa pag interview ko sa mga opsiyal ng gobyerno eto lang masasabi ko- kulang pa nga itong ginagawa ko sa tindi ng sakripisyo ng mga government officials natin lalo na nga ating Pangulo. Halos karamihan sa kanila lagpas dose oras sa trabaho dahil nga pressured sila sa atin. Dahil ang Pangulo natin ay nangako ng tunay na pagbabago. Kaya mga kaDDS kung gusto niyong makatulong din sa kanila pag may nakita kayong good news share niyo sa lahat ng friends niyo. Tayo nalang ang inaasahan ng DUTERTE ADMINISTRATION. At sa inyo po Sec MannyPi√±ol mabuhay po kayo!

Mga Pagbabago sa DAR (Dept. of Agrarian Reform) 
#100DaysofChange

Noong Oct. 7 tayo po ay naimbitahan sa Cultural Night ng mga magsasaka sa gymnasium ng DAR. Sa Duterte Administration unang nakapasok ang ating mga magsasaka sa DAR at nagkaroon ng ganitong klaseng pagtitipon makalipas ng labing walong taong sila'y hinarangan ng mga barikada. Ayon sa aking panayam kay DAR Sec. Ka Paeng Mariano isa sa pinaka malaking achievement ni Pangulong Duterte ay ang pag-reconvene o pag-assembly muli ng PARC (Presidential Agrarian Reform Council) noong Sept. 12, 2016 (makalipas ng 10 taon) na kung saan ang mismong Chair ay ang ating Pangulo. Ang layunin ng PARC ay proteksyonan ang interes ng mga magsasaka na sila'y hindi mapapatalsik sa kanilang lupa. Marahil ito na ang isa sa aking pinaka paboritong nagawa ni P. DUTERTE sa kanyang unang 100 days bilang Pangulo. Ito ay isang patunay na si P. DUTERTE ay may tunay na malasakit sa ating mga ordinaryong mamamayang Pilipino.

CREDIT GRABBING ISSUE

Just to clear it out, my post regarding NAIA terminal 1 points on the improvements not on the rehabilitation of the terminal which was done during Aquino administration. The improvements I am talking about is not about the surface renovation that was done by previous admin. I am highlighting the better customer service that you can now experience. Thanks to a concerned citizen (who opted to remain anonymous,) I was made aware on a post by an anti-duterte group saying I posted fake news. And there were comments saying I'm grabbing credit that should be for the previous administration. Here are just some things I would like to point out.

1) You call yourselves Thinking class, alam niyo naman na "Improvement" does not mean "Renovation", di ba? What's your basis that my post was about the renovation made by previous admin? Dahil sa picture?  Wow, nag-iisip nga kayo. 
If you will view my video interview with the officials in NAIA you will see that I am highlighting on the improving services of the airport at hindi sa pagpapaganda lamang ng airport. Hindi kasi sapat na maganda lng tignan ang airport, dapat pati services sa mga tao maasyos din. At yan ang improvement na sinasabi ko.

2) Kahit na narenovate nga ang NAIA terminal 1, merong mga complaints with regards to customer service, mahabang pila, at crowded seating areas. And these are the improvement I am saying.

Link: http://cnnphilippines.com/lifestyle/2015/10/20/NAIA-Manila-no-longer-2015-worst-airport-travel.html

3) My personal blog is not a news blog, I never claim that I report news. I just choose to highlight things which are not being published by news site or DAD (Die-hard Anti- Duterte) pages.

Lastly, you call me credit grabber, wow BIG word. Here are some articles kung sino ba ang pinakasikat na Credit grabber (Hint: Dilaw to)

Now compare him to P. Duterte. Ang hirap kasi noon, ang presidente natin si alyas boy sisi eh. Sisi doon, sisi dito. While our current president focuses on the solution to our country's problems.

Ipinaabot din natin sa kanya ang mga katanungan at hinaing ng mga ordinaryong Pilipino. Sa kalagitnaan ng interview si GM Ed Monreal ay napaluha nang aking tinanong sa kanya kung ano ang kanyang reaksyon sa mga nagsasabing "credit grabbing" lang daw ang DUTERTE ADMINISTRATION. Nakakalungkot dahil sa kabila ng pag-double time sa trabaho ng bawat ahensya ng gobyerno tulad ng DOTr (Sec. Arthur Tugade) sila pa ay naaakusahan ng ganito. KWENTONG BARBERO - PART 2 (TAGALOG VERSION)
by: Pamela Saavedra
Isang araw sa Davao City, nagpapahinga si Angkol Barber sa kanyang barbershop.
Angkol: Haay, ang hirap nitong tumatanda tayo. Masakit na ang likod. Ang masaklap, wala pang customer.
Maya-maya, dumating si Tikboy kasama ang kaibigan niyang si Mikmik.
Tikboy: Kol!
Angkol: O, ikaw yung nagpagupit kahapon ah.
Tikboy: Oo, kol.
Angkol: O bakit ka bumalik? Anong sa atin?
Tikboy: Magpapagupit kami,kol. Itong kasama ko.
Angkol: Ah ganun ba. Halika, dito tayo.
Umupo si Mikmik.
Angkol: Anong gupit nito?
Tikboy: Mohawk yang sa kanya, kol. Pero gunting lang gamitin mo, wag electric shaver.
Angkol: Naku, aabutin tayo ng bukas nyan.
Tikboy: Okay lang kol, para mahaba-haba yung kwentuhan.
Angkol: Ay, ano ba ito? Magpapagupit ba kayo o makikipagkwentuhan?
Tikboy: Nag-usap kasi kami na magpapagupit din siya sayo pero hati kami. Tig-singkwenta kami para P100.
Angkol: Ah sige. Okay lang sakin. Mabuti naman kasi mahina ang kita ko ngayon.
Inumpisahan ni Angkol ang paggugupit kay Mikmik.
Tikboy: Kinwento ko sa kanya yung kinwento niyo po sa akin kahapon, kol. Ayaw niya kasing maniwala.
Angkol: Sabi ko nga sayo, kwentong barbero lang yun. Depende lang yan sayo kung maniniwala ka o hindi.
Tikboy: Yun nga sabi ko sa kanya, kol. Pero may mga tanong kasi siya na hirap akong sagutin. Kaya dinala ko siya rito.
Angkol: Ano yung tanong mo dong?
Mikmik: Ikaw nalang, Boy. (Mahinang boses)
Tikboy: Pasensya ka na kol. Mahiyain kasi itong batang to. Bakit daw nasabi mo na namumulubi na ang America?
Angkol: Aaah, ganun ba. Sige, sige. Pakiabot nga ng cellphone ko.
Tikboy: (Inabot ang cellphone kay Angkol)
Angkol: Search mo dyan, usdebtclock.org
Tikboy: May wifi pala dito kol?
Angkol: Oo. Sa City Hall yan galing.
Tikboy: (Nagsearch si Tikboy) Andaming numbers nito kol. Hindi ko maintindihan to.
Angkol: Tingnan mo yung sa gitna. Yang US Gross Domestic Product. Ilan yan?
Tikboy: Eighteen... Eighteen... Ilan ito? Million? Billion?
Angkol: Trillion. $18.5 trillion.
Tikboy: Talaga?
Angkol: Yang sa taas, tingnan mo yan. US National Debt.
Tikboy: $19.5 trillion. Hala!
Angkol: Yan ang sinasabi ko. So paano ka makakabawi kung mas malaki pa utang mo kesa sa income?
Tikboy: Ang saklap. Tapos anong ginagawa nilang solusyun para diyan, kol?
Angkol: Kaya nga nagkakandarapa na sila ngayon. Muntik nang gumuho ang ekonomiya nila dahil sa recession nung 2008.
Tikboy: Bakit nag survive pa sila?
Angkol: Kasi panay print nila ng dollar. Habang may dolyar, maraming bansa ang nagpapapalit nito kasi yan ang world reserve currency. Pero yung utang nila, grabe din ang paglobo. Para yang time bomb na mahirap pigilan. Natatakot na ang gobyerno nila dahil lagi nalang nilang itinataas ang "debt ceiling" o yung limit ng utang. Hanggang sa nagpanic na talaga. Alam mo bang nagshutdown ang US Federal Government taong 2013 dahil ang diyan sa utang? Saan ka nakakita ng gobyernong nag shutdown dahil sa utang? Ganyan kalaki ang problemang yan.
Mikmik: (Pinagpawisan)
Tikboy: Tapos bumibili tayo ng dolyar, wala naman pala yang halaga?
Angkol: Kaya nga sinabi ko sayo kahapon na "fiat money". Kilala mo ba si Gaddafi?
Tikboy: Hindi, kol.
Angkol: Yung lider ng Libya. Yan kasi ang plano niya na itigil ang palitan ng dolyar. Ang gusto niya ay magtrade sa oil gamit ang gold. O, asan na siya ngayon? Patay na. Search mo diyan sa youtube "we came, we saw, he died."
Tikboy: Loko, si Clinton to ah. Bakit tuwang-tuwa siya na namatay si Gaddafi?
Angkol: Aba'y syempre. Dahil wala nang hahadlang sa mga plano nila.
Mikmik: (Napabilib si Mikmik)
Tikboy: Yung oil na malapit na daw maubos. Bakit niyo daw po nasabi yun?
Angkol: Yun, posible talaga yun. Hindi kasi renewable energy ang oil. Ibig sabihin, hindi napapalitan ng bago. Di magtatagal, mauubos din yan. Fossil fuel kasi yan. Pero yung sasabihin mong malapit nang maubos ang oil sa mundo, classified na info yan. Pinapatay ang may mga info about dyan. Yung sinabi nilang suicide daw ni Michael Ruppert, hindi ako naniniwalang suicide yon.
Tikboy: Sino yan siya kol?
Angkol: Basta.
Tikboy: (Naintriga)
Angkol: Tandaan mo, dong. Ang biggest trade deal in world history ay hindi pinublish ng Western Media.
Tikboy: Ano yun kol?
Angkol: "China-Russia Gas Deal of 2015".
Tikboy: (Tumahimik lang. Walang na gets)
Angkol: Diba sabi ko sayo papaubos na ang oil? Kaya ambilis kumilos ng China ang nagpakonekta kaagad ng pipeline sa Russia. Ang Russia kasi ang pinakamalaking supplier ng natural gas sa buong mundo. Ang natural gas ay renewable, ang oil hindi. Kaya nga ang Russia ay isa sa pinakamakapangyarihang bansa sa buong mundo. Kaya yang propaganda nilang papanig daw si Duterte sa Russia at China dahil communist daw? Wala talaga silang alam. Sa di kalayuan, ang Russia at China ang magdadala sa kontinente ng Asya. At alam ng Presidente natin yan. Kung hindi sasabay ang Pilipinas, kawawa tayo. Tayo ang magsisisi. Kung sakali man dong na pumanaw na ako sa mundong ito, baka maabutan mong tayo na ang tutulong sa Western countries. Alam mo ba kung bakit? Dahil may sarili tayong natural gas dito. Sa Liguasan Marsh, sa Agusan Marsh at sa ibang lugar sa Pilipinas. Yang si Digong, sinasabi lang nyang 75 lang daw siya pero hindi lang nila alam. Daig pa ang taga Wharton niyan sa talino.
Tikboy: Grabe kol, ano?
Angkol: Kaya ayaw talagang ipagpalit ni Duterte yan nang dahil lang sa "aid" ng America. Dahil ang kinabukasan ng Pilipinas ang nakasalalay diyan. Ang problema kasi ng ibang Pinoy, takot na palitan ang status quo. Proud yan sila na talagang Westernized ang Pilipinas. Masakit sa kanila ang baguhin yan. Kung makikipagtalo ka, English-englisan ka para sila ang tama. Hindi talaga nila matanggap na ang Presidente ay isang taga-Mindanao, isang Bisaya na gustong kumalas sa Western Powers.
Tikboy: (Sumang-ayon)
Angkol: They see us as beggars or "mendicants" as what the President calls it. Why give us aid when we can be trading partners? Why stay as a puppet when we can be independent and build a strong nation of our own? When was the last time you stood up and held your head high as a Filipino? Be proud of who you are and tell that to the world. I am a Filipino. I am a Bisaya and I am proud of my thick accent - strong and fearless like the great Lapu-lapu! I am a Muslim and I am proud to wear my hijab. We are the unconquered people who last defended the island of Mindanao! I am a Tagalog and the blood of our national heroes flow in me! I am an Aeta and my ancestors scaled the mountains of the great Sierra Madre long before civilization was born in these lands! I am a Badjao and we are the fearless masters of the sea! Again, when was the last time you were proud to be a Filipino? Hala, hala! Teka muna, teka muna...
Tikboy: Hala Mik!
Angkol: Punasan mo ng towel.
Tikboy: (Pinunasan ang ilong ni Mikmik gamit ang Good Morning towel)
Tikboy: Hahaha! Dumudugo ilong mo Mik! Hahaha!
Mikmik: Gago ka.
Tikboy: Hahaha! 
Angkol: Anong nangyari sayo dong? O sya, tapusin na natin to.
At natapos ang pagpapagupit ni Mikmik.
Tikboy: Kol, salamat. (Sabay abot ng P100)
Angkol: Naku, salamat din dong.
Tikboy: Opo kol! Marami pa akong tanong pero sa susunod na naman. Balik lang kami.
Angkol: Sige, ingat kayo. Wag kayong parating laro ng laro ng computer. At higit sa lahat, wag talaga kayong papasok dyan sa droga. Mag-aral kayong mabuti. Malay natin baka isa sa inyo ang magiging susunod na Presidente ng Pilipinas.
Tikboy: Hindi kol. Gusto naming maging barbero!

"Duterte ally, women's groups call for end of drug-related slays"

This was the headline used by ABS-CBN in their recent article and interview with DSWD sec. Judy Taguiwalo.

While it is true that DSWD sec. Taguiwalo said that they do not tolerate extra judicial killing (who does, anyways? You're making it out like the president is promoting extra judicial killings while his clear order was to kill drug suspects when they fight back) she also mentioned in her facebook account that they were originally invited to talk about "social protection programs, and DSWD's role in the rehabilitation of the drug victims".

 a person employed by a newspaper, magazine, or television company to gather and report news (2) :  a person who broadcasts news

MY OPINION ON EJK SENATE HEARING & DE LIMA's WALK OUT DRAMA

I am not a Political analyst nor a Journalist, sinasabi ko lang kung ano mismo ang nakikita ko (sa nakikita ko personally, sa balita, o sa personal message ng ibang concerned citizens.) I believe that President Duterte is a leader we can unite behind because he is someone who will also have our backs basta tayo ang nasa tama. Regardless of his flaws, I choose to support his actions and do my part in ensuring faster implementations of his programs instead of just criticizing him pero yun lang naman ang ginawa. Tanong ko lang, makakatulong ba sa pagunlad ng bansa ang puro criticism pero wala kang ginagawa on your part?

I'm not against the senate hearing about the alleged cases of Extra Judicial Killing and President Duterte has also stated before that he is against EJK. Pero if this hearing is not a political attack from the "Minions" politician, then why did the hearing suddenly shift from Extra Judicial Killing (Cops killing criminal without due process issue,) which is the MAIN reason they conducted this hearing by the way, to Duterte's involvement with the so-called Davao Death Squad or DDS. I thought the Senate hearing about EJK was held to investigate whether or not the police are executing suspects on the spot, and to expedite the police efforts in resolving the vigilante killings; but it turned out to be a way for the "Minions" to attack and disgrace P. Duterte.  Why didn't they do this before when he was still just a mayor or just running for the presidency, hawak na ng DOJ si Matobato noon pa, and if they have done it during that time they could have filed a case against P.Duterte since he was not yet a president at the time. And now, Sen. De Lima wants an academic discussion about rethinking the president's immunity from law suits? Hindi  DAW about kay P. Duterte yan. Masiyadong Obvious!

In the recent Senate hearing naman, it looks like Sen. De Lima is living up to her reputation as the walk out queen. Well, yes, your feelings might have been hurt because of the accusations they are throwing at you, accusations that according to you have no basis but isn't true that your accusation towards P. Duterte is solely based on a single unreliable witness? Besides, you're a Senator now, you have a job to do, and you are still a member of a senate committee inquiring about EJK (that you used to throw your accusations at the president). Remember when you and Sen. Trillanes ganged up on Sen. Cayetano? He stayed there and defended himself; he did not avoid any confrontation because he knows he's right, and even if he was overpowered then he continued to do his job, same job that you took when you won as Senator. Woman up and engage in intellectual debate with your colleagues IF you really believe what you're saying, stop walking out from the hearing and going to the camera to gain sympathy.

No law degree, OPINION only.  About sa issue ng concealing material evidence, it's just my belief that the senators involved in the hearing, especially the members of the committee, must be informed beforehand about the case NBI filed against Matobato. The transcripts that Sen. Trillanes brought did show that Matobato disclosed that there was a KFR case filed against him but not all the details about the case are there and besides you interviewed him before you presented him to the senate committee, the question is why you didn't inform your colleagues about it ahead of time. Isn't part of your duty as Senate committee chairman then?

AGAIN I have No Law degree, Not a Journalist or a Political analyst. Just asking. Just stating my opinions. Just a simple civilian who wants to make a difference. A simple civilian who wants to help steer our country towards a better future. Para sa tunay na pagbabago!

REPOST FROM CNN

Metro Manila (CNN Philippines) ‚Äî Starting this September, the combat-duty pay of police and military personnel surges to a fixed ‚Ç±3,000 per month under Executive Order (E.O.) No. 3 issued by President Rodrigo Duterte on Monday.

The President's directive is a six-fold increase from the former combat duty pay (‚Ç±500 per month) of qualified Armed Forces of the Philippines (AFP) troops.

It is also an 882 percent surge from the former combat duty pay (‚Ç±340 per month) of the Philippine National Police (PNP).

E.O. No. 3 provides combat incentive pay for PNP personnel and increases that of the AFP. Members of both organizations can now earn at least ‚Ç±300 per day but no more than ‚Ç±3,000 per month.

Previously, AFP personnel could only earn ‚Ç±150 per day, but no more than ‚Ç±1,500 per operations order or fragmentary order.

Combat incentive pay is given to personnel of the AFP and PNP who "figure directly in actual combat against members of various insurgent, terrorist and lawless elements."

According to the executive order, initial funding will come from the President's Miscellaneous Personnel Benefits Fund. Succeeding funding will be included in the specific budgets of the PNP and AFP through the General Appropriations Act, provided that both organizations submit respective rosters of personnel.

"The validated list shall be the basis for allocating funds for the purpose in the succeeding years," the directive said.

BREAKING NEWS:

MONEY TRAIL SHOWS P38-M DEPOSITS WENT TO LEILA DRIVER'S KIN

MANILA, Philippines ‚Äì The Department of Justice has collated bank documents allegedly showing that over P38 million in cash deposits were made to the bank accounts of two relatives of Sen. Leila de Lima's driver and reported lover in 2014.

This information came out during the DOJ's fact-finding investigation on the illegal drug operations in the New Bilibid Prison when De Lima was secretary of justice. 

The STAR obtained bank deposit slips showing that millions of pesos went to the bank accounts of Hannah Mae Dayan and Marco Palisoc ‚Äì daughter and cousin of Ronnie Dayan, respectively. 

The DOJ has forwarded the bank records to the Anti-Money Laundering Council for verification, according to a well-placed source.

Dayan's account received P24 million in four cash deposits ‚Äì P3 million on Feb. 7, 2014; P9 million on Feb. 21, 2014; P6 million on March 14, 2014 and P6 million on March 28, 2014.

Palisoc's account got P14,304,000 in two cash deposits ‚Äì P9,600,000 on Sept. 16, 2014 and P4,704,000 on Oct. 23, 2014.
 
Justice Secretary Vitaliano Aguirre II earlier revealed that investigators have gathered bank deposit slips of several staff of De Lima and people linked to her totaling to over P88 million.

Other bank records showed cash deposits in accounts of De Lima's former staff Jonathan Caranto (P24 million), Bogs Obuyes (P24 million) and Marrel Obuyes (P2.2 million). 

Aguirre asked the AMLC to verify the deposits amid suspicion that some quarters were out to sabotage the DOJ probe and feed investigators with wrong information.

The DOJ received the AMLC report last week, but Aguirre did not divulge the findings due to the Bank Secrecy Law.

He only hinted that the report covered more than 10 people he branded as "friends of De Lima."

"If there is any link (between drug money and De Lima), it's indirect ‚Äì only bank accounts of her companions, friends and employees," he said.

"But these people have no big sources of income to get millions in deposits, so what other conclusion could you get?" 

Aguirre also revealed that probers are also verifying information that about P500 million in drug money went to a duly registered corporation doing business in the national penitentiary. He did not name the firm pending probe.

He also would not reveal what the DOJ would do next with the AMLC report ‚Äì if it could be used to seek a freeze order from the Court of Appeals.

"For now, this AMLC report will be for our use to further our investigation until a case is filed in court," he said.

Aguirre believes that the money trail would bolster the testimonial evidence from high-profile NBP inmates against De Lima.

"We asked for additional reports because we received so many bank account numbers," he said. "We're just in the first wave. As I said earlier, the information is just overflowing." 

In the House of Representatives inquiry, high-profile inmates led by robbery and carjack convict Herbert Colanggo claimed that they gave millions of payola to De Lima for protection of their illicit businesses and activities in the NBP.

Aguirre said he has tapped the National Bureau of Investigation to pursue the probe as more witnesses are set to be presented before the House.

Dayan has been subpoenaed to appear before the House, but he could not be located.

Sa madaling salita HINDI KASALANAN NI P.DUTERTE ang pagbagsak ng Stock Market. Wag po tayong maniwala sa ibang tao. Mismong PSE Director na ang nagsabi na hindi kasalanan ni P.Duterte. 

DUTERTE'S 'FOUL MOUTH' NOT REASON FOR FOREIGN SELLOFF, SAYS PSE DIRECTOR
MANILA - President Rodrigo Duterte's tough rhetoric and cursing aren't the reason for the foreign selloff in the Philippine stock market, one of the directors of the Philippine Stock Exchange (PSE) said on Friday.
Foreign selling is caused by the strengthening dollar and some investors betting that the US Federal Reserve will increase interest rates, said Vivian Yuchengo, president of the Philippine Association of Stock Brokers and Dealers Inc.
Yuchengo said foreign selling began even before Duterte threatened to curse at US President Barack Obama in a speech before he left for the ASEAN summit in Laos.
"It was already 10 days before that when money started leaving because the dollar was very strong, and so the funds were moving to the [United] States because they were anticipating a rate hike," she told dzMM.
Foreign portfolio investments posted net outflows of $600,000 on Thursday, bringing the weekly total to $34.3 million and the monthly total to $344.8 million, according to Bloomberg data.
The selloff is also caused by investors taking a pro-dollar position as the peso continues to weaken.
The peso weakened on Friday to P47.99 to a dollar, its lowest level since January 26, as regional currencies tracked a weak yen following the US Federal Reserve's decision to hold interest rates.
"[Investors] were expecting higher rates, so they'll get higher rates in return for their money rather than here. But then it didn't happen, so very little is leaving the country now," she said.
The selloff also occurred during the "ghost month" in August, when historically the stock market dips, she added.
Other ASEAN countries are also experiencing outflows due to similar factors, Yuchengco said, noting that other nations "don't have a Duterte."
Meanwhile, Finance Secretary Sonny Dominguez said he doesn't see investors heading for the exit.
Top executives of the World Bank, Japan International Cooperation Agency, Asian Development Bank, and the ambassadors of Spain, China and the European Union are "bullish on the Philippine economy and were in accord that the Duterte administration could sustain the economic overdrive," Dominguez said.
"We must not get distracted by the political noise. There's a lot of good things ahead for our country and our economy on the Duterte watch," he added.

Tunay Na Pagbabago

Isa po sa magiging programa ng DRUG REHAB na ating pong inaayos ay ang pagababalik loob sa ating Panginoon ng mga kababayan nating nasira ng droga. Naniniwala po ako na ang tunay na pagbabago ay nagsisimuala sa loob - puso at kaluluwa ng tao. Marami pong programa tayong hinahanda para sa mga papasok sa rehab - livelihood, education and skills training, recreation, moral and spiritual activities. Pero para sa akin ang pinaka importante ay ang pagbabalik loob sa ating Panginoon. Habang may buhay ang tao maaari itong magbago kahit anong lulong nito sa droga dahil sa Panginoon ay walang impossible. Super excited na po ako dito sa proyekto nating ito. FROM MY EMAIL
ATTENTION Department of Environment and Natural Resources (DENR) Department of Tourism - Philippines Kat De Castro DILG Central Office Boracay Island, The Philippines

ANO NA NANGYAYARI SA BORACAY
 
Hi Ms Mocha

First I would like to thank you for all your efforts and undying support to our president. You have made an impact to many Filipinos, all your hard work and effort are deeply appreciated. Hindi ko na po pahahabin and gagawin ko lang bullet points ang mga concerns ko.

Last August 24-26 I attended a convention in Boracay. And I'm excited because our singaporean boss is coming with us in this event. It will be his first time in boracay and we are very proud to show him the island. But when we arrived I'm embarrased and very disappointed. We check in at a very nice hotel in station 2. Maganda ang service and facility and all. Pero I was shocked when I saw the view in the back of our hotel eto ung picture.
1.Ok fine na dinedevelop natin ung island pero commercialism is destroying it ang daming mga tinatayo na hotels and establishment pero naiiwan ng mga basura nila nagcause ng baha sa lugar.

2. Grabe ang nagkalat na basura. Sa beach at sa shore.
May mag nagkalat mineral water bottles slippers at kung ano ano pa.

3. Walang proper disposal ng basura as in walang garabe can 
hindi ko kinaya ms mocha wala pang 5mins ako nag swimming sa beach umahon ako kasi may katabi ako sachet ng datu puti suka!
I'm sure kung apo ni Ms Gina Lopez na 2 years old hindi niya pagsswimming ang bata.

4. Dapat dito i impose ang no plastic imagine the magnitude of waste one establishment produce
Taken at McDonalds Boracay

5. Nasan napupunta ang mag environmental fees na binabayad ng mga visitors?

6. Sobrang daming foreigner na chinese and koreans at kung makapagkalat sila grabe. Hindi nila magawa sa lugar nila kaya dito ata sila nag kakalat. Sa Japan or Singapore bawal magkalat may fine dapat impose din yan lalo na sa mga tourist spots natin.

7. Eto mam wala naman po akong masamang tinapay pero sobrang daming hookers and gay hookers. They are very agressive. 9pm pa lang andun na sila. One night na lumabas magisa ang sinaporean kong boss natakot daw siya kasi kinokorner siya ng 5 gay na hookers tumakbo siya pabalik sa hotel.Daig pa natin ang Thailand, hindi siya healthly kung lalabas kami mag didinner na may kasamang bata tapos ganun ang nakikita nila. Also walang visibility ang police pag gabi di mo maramdaman.

This is not my first time sa Boracay, very special ang place na ito for me. Dito nag propose yung husband ko sakin kaya malapit ang lugar na ito sa puso ko. Pero mam kung hindi ito gagawan ng paraan give it 5 years masisira na ang island. I think masyadong concerns and DENR na puro minahan na lang pinupuntirya nila napaka laking concern ang basura at sinabi ito sa SONA ni President Duterte. I understand na need natin ang tourism pero kung hindi tayo magiging mahigpit masisira ang tourist spots natin dapat makita na responsible din tayo pangalagaan ito. REPOST FROM Krizette Laureta Chu 

I- tag po natin ang The New York Times mga ka-DDS so they can hear the VOICE of the  91% FILIPINOS WHO SUPPORT P. DUTERTE's WAR ON DRUGS!! Share po natin mga ka-DDS!

Dear The New York Times:

As a huge fan of your newspaper, I know you will never accept payment from any group to bring down Duterte. But I do want a few answers from you, but because I am a nobody, just a Filipino citizen concerned for the future of my country, I highly encourage our government--when it starts its legal proceedings against De Lima--to ask this from you:

1. Why do you allow a Filipino writer to use a nom de plume for an article as sensitive as the ones that are coming out? The ones that are damaging for this country. Why get somebody who cannot even stand by his own name, let alone stand by his story? What are your policies for this?

2. People need to know the truth behind the production of the Matobato video. Who produced, shot, and conceptualized the video of Matobato? Did Richard Paddock, Asia bureau chief, commission the video team that produced it? Or was it presented and given to you--SUBTITLES INCLUDED!--by freelancers? Was it given to you for free (hence, a press release) or did you have to pay for it (peddled to the highest bidder)?
In the video, Matobato's hair is very short, and yet, in the hearing, it is long, almost shaggy. How many months were you sitting on this video? How long before the hearing did you shoot this video? Why did you wait until the day of the hearing to release it? Who had the power to give you the go-signal? 

When your stories destabilize a country (not purposely on your part, I am sure), when your answers will aid us to get to the bottom of a certain issue, when your response will help us determine and uncover a plot that threatens to divert us from finding out the truth about government officials that should be held liable for criminal acts,   then I am sure you do not want to be tagged as accomplice.

Please do not allow people with vested interests to besmirch your great name by doing your job well. Your desk editors should fact check, double-triple fact check, even call the persons named in the story to check for the veracity of every information and detail presented there. Please do not leave it up to your contributors.

To you, this may just be another story. For the Philippines, this is our future. 

Thank you.

Respectfully, 

A concerned citizen of the Republic of the Philippines

I'd rather have a "colorful" President than a "DISENTE" President who does nothing but steal money from people and protect the DRUG LORDS.

MY OFFICIAL STATEMENT REGARDING MOCHA GIRLS PERFORMING AT A CONCERT IN BILIBID

Totoo po na noong late 2012 or early 2013 kami po ay nagperform sa bilibid. Marami pong nag perform doon sa event na yun. Ito po ay pormal na concert na dumaan po sa tamang proseso. Marami pong mga artista na nagsho-show dun at nagbibigay pag-asa sa mga bilanggo. Sa tingin ko naman po walang masama kung ito ay PORMAL na nanggaling sa opisyal ng BUCOR. Ang Mocha Girls ay involved po sa iba't ibang charity shows kahit noon pa man. Binibigyan lamang ito ng kulay ng ibang ANTI-DUTERTE dahil kami ay suporter ng ating Pangulo. Itong mga DILAW na ito ay hindi na maipagtanggol si De Lima kaya kung anu-anong issue ang gustong ungkatin. Tulad ng nabanggit ng witness, maraming mga artists ang nakapagperform na doon kasama na si SHARON CUNETA at FREDDIE AGUILAR. Ang nakakapagtaka lang ay bakit kami lang ang idinidiin at binibigyan ng kulay. Una sa lahat, hindi ko po kinahihiya iyon bakit? Tulad nga ng aking sinabi, walang masama kung ito ay dumaan sa tamang paraan. And for argument's sake, kung bawal pala iyon hindi dapat ang mga Artista o Entertainer ang sisihin dapat ang pamunuan ng BUCOR at dating SEC DE LIMA dahil sila ang nag issue ng kaukulang permit upang makapag concert sa loob. Ngunit uulitin ko hindi ko ikinahihiya ito dahil ako at ang aking grupo ay nagbigay ng malinis na kasiyahan at pag-asa sa mga taong nagkamali sa lipunan. Ngayon po ako ay abala sa pagsisimula ng isang foundation na magtatayo ng mga REHAB CENTERS sa iba't ibang bahagi ng Pilipinas. Natural na ako po ay magpe-perform ng WALANG BAYAD kasama ang buong Mocha Girls upang magbigay ng pag-asa sa mga, uulitin ko, NAGKAMALI SA LIPUNAN. Dahil ako ay naniniwala na habang may buhay ang tao ito ay may pag-asang maayos at maging kapanipakinabang sa lipunan. At hindi ko ikinahihiya ito. 

Ang tamang tanong dito ay - sa dinami dami ng mga nag concert sa Bilibid na mga artista bakit ang kailangan idiin at gawan ng issue ay kami? Simple, POLITIKA! Dahil kami ay masugid na suporter ni Pangulong Duterte.  At magandang i-SENSATIONALIZE ng MEDIA at BLOG/FB PAGE ang issue na ito. 

Sa mga UTAK DILAW, ibalik natin ang issue- 
DE LIMA, TOTOO BA NA IKAW AY TUMATANGGAP NG PAYOLA SA MGA INMATE? Kung HINDI sagutin mo isa-isa ang akusasyon sayo.

Noong nanalo si Tatay Digong bilang Pangulo sabi ng ilang Duterte Supporters, "it's time to unite". Personally, hindi po ako kumbinsido sa naging panawagan na yun. Naniniwala ako na kung gaano tayo kainit sa pagsuporta kay Tatay Digong noong panahon ng kampanya dapat ay mas maging maiinit pa ngayong Pangulo na siya. Kaya ako po ay naglabas ng open letter para kay VP LENI. Marami ang nagalit sa akin dahil dito at kung anu ano na ang sinabi sa akin. Kesyo bakit daw ayaw ko ng UNITY, it's time to heal daw, huwag na akong maging war freak, etc. Sa katunayan sa isang SOCIAL MEDIA gathering ng mga supporters ni P.Duterte akin din pong sinabi na kailangan panatilihin natin ang apoy dahil hindi titigil ang mga DILAW na itulak ang PLAN B. Marami tuloy ang nagsabi na OA na daw ako. Ngayon, hindi lang ako ang nagsasabing may PLAN B. Pati na ang ating Pangulo, si Sen. Alan Cayetano at marami pang iba. Hirit ng mga DILAW na kesyo "CRAZY" daw ako kasi praning daw ako. Para po sa kaalaman ng iba, hindi lang po ako post ng post dito ng walang basehan. Ako po ay nagsasaliksik at kumakausap ng mga tao. Hindi ko lamang po pwedeng sabihin ang mga sources ko po dahil hindi po ako authorized na banggitin ang kanilang mga pangalan.

Kaya paulit ulit ko pong sinasabi na tayo dapat ay maging mainit sa pagsuporta sa ating Pangulo.Bakit? Tandaan natin ang mga elemento ng pagbagsak ng isang gobyerno sa atin-
1.Media.  Local at International, ito ay minamanipula na ng mga DILAW.   
2.Simbahan. Alam naman natin hanggang ngayon nasa Dilaw ang simbahan. 
3.Sundalo. Ito ay ating kakampi sa ngayon. Kaya tayo ay dapat maging aktibo sa usaping Peace Talks at pagpapaalis ng Amerikano sa Mindanao.  Dahil may ilang sundalo ang tutol dito. 
4.Ipapalit na Lider.  Kaya hindi nakakapagtaka na puro PR ang VP natin. 
5.MASS SUPPORT. Sa ngayon ito ay 91% pa sa ating Pangulo. Kaya nalang aktibo ang mga TROLL sa Social Media upang ipakita na may suporta kuno ang DILAW. 

Hindi pa tapos ang laban mga ka-DDS! Huwag tayong pumayag na basta-basta nilang patalsikin ang pinaghirapan nating lahat na iniluklok na Pangulo na si DUTERTE!

THE ROCK PRESIDENT

It is too early to tell but if all goes well by 2022, we might be looking at the next military man to become President.

The first, of course was General Emilio Aguinaldo who fought for our independence from Spain in 1898 and became President of the First Philippine Republic. The second was Ferdinand Marcos who was a soldier during World War II, a lawyer and later Senator before becoming President in 1963. Third, who would ever forget the man who smoked Havana cigars - Fidel Ramos. He graduated from the U.S. Military Academy at West Point, a Korean war veteran, a general before becoming a politician and later President in 1992.

If General Ronald "Bato" Dela Rosa can pass with flying colors the big test of curbing crime and the drug problem in this country, he might be regarded as another savior and the same enthusiasm and political fanaticism felt by the people on his predecessor will catapult him to the presidency. His success in the next six years will shape his destiny.

Mayroon akong nasagap noon na balita na ang kalaban ni Pangulong DUTERTE ay nagsisimula ng kumilos. Hindi ko po kaagad ito pinost dahil gusto ko po muna makasigurado dahil ayaw ko po magkalat ng tsismis o haka haka lamang. Nagtanong muna ako sa mga taong naka paligid sa ating Pangulo para makasigurado. Ngayon, sunud sunod na ang kanilang atake sa ating Pangulo. Ganito ang sistema ng mga kalaban. Dahil more than 90% ang approval rating ng ating Pangulo ay hindi kaya ng kalaban na siraan ang ating Pangulo dito sa sarili nating bansa. Kaya ang gagawin nila ay ang tinatawag na "BACKDOOR" ATTACK. Yan ay ang siraan si Pangulong Duterte sa International scene.  Sa madaling salita, sa ibang bansa magkakalat ng lagim ang mga kalaban. Palalabasin nila na masamang imahe ang ating Pangulo at ang mga nangyayari sa ating bansa. Habang ang LOCAL MEDIA ay patuloy na idinidiin ang EXTRAJUDICIAL KILLINGS kay P. DUTERTE ito naman ang pini-PICK UP na balita ng INTERNATIONAL MEDIA. At yan ay nagsimula na. At dahil dito babagsak ang negosyo o ekonomiya natin. May ilang mga negosyante na natatakot na dito sa Pilipinas dahil pinalalabas ng mga POLITIKO, SIMBAHAN at MEDIA na ang PILIPINAS ay isang MALAKING KILLING FIELD. Pag bumagsak ang ekonomiya ay susunod na ang pagbaba ng moral ng mga supporters ni P.Duterte. Isa pa sa kanilang gagawin ay aatakihin nila ang mga INFLUENCERS sa SOCIAL MEDIA para ito ay ma-discredit. Marami sa mga GENUINE PRO-DUTERTE PAGE ay madalas atakihin. Sa katunayan gumagawa pa sila ng mga ANTI-DUTERTE PAGE para lamang tirahin ang mga PRO-DUTERTE PAGE. Hindi ko na babanggitin kung anong mga ANTI-DUTERTE PAGES na nagsulputan para idiscredit o atakahin ang mga tulad ni Thinking Pinoy, Sass Roganda Sasot, Lapu Lapu at ilang pang PRO-DUTERTE page. Meron pa nga akong nabalitaan na sila ay nagha-hire pa ng mga SOCIAL MEDIA WARRIORS na kasing laki ng isang call center para lamang bantayan at ireport ang mga PRO-DUTERTE Page. Meron pa nga akong nasagap na balita na may isang ANTI-DUTERTE PAGE na ginawa para lamang banatan ang aking Page. Sigurado ako alam niyo na yan. Hindi ko na babanggitin baka sumikat pa siya. 
Maraming nagagawang magagandang proyekto ang ating Gobyerno ngayon tulad ng mga ginagawa ng DOTr, BOC, DSWD, Tax Reform at maging Peace Talks. Ngunit ito ay natatabunan dahil sa kampanya ng mga kalaban ni P.Duterte. Tulad na lang ng bombings, EJK, pagmumura at kung anu ano pang mga issue. May nabalitaan din po ako na hinahanda na nila ang pampalit sa ating PANGULO. Pinababango na nila ang IMAHE nito sa iba't ibang bansa. 
ANO PO BA ANG ATING MAAARING GAWIN?? Tulad nga ng sinabi ni SEN. CAYETANO, don't underestimate the power of PRAYER. Totoo po yan kasi sa totoo lang nakakaawa na si Tatay Digong. Pagud na pagod na siya kakatrabaho para umayus ang bansa natin pero itong mga AMBISYOSONG POLITIKO ay hindi tumitigil sa paninira sa kanya. IPANALANGIN NATIN SI TATAY DIGONG at ipagpatuloy natin ang LABAN SA SOCIAL MEDIA. Mag bantay, mag matyag at maging aktibo sa pag-share, pag-comment, at pagpaliwanag sa ating mga kamag-anak/kaibigan lalo na yung mga nasa ibang bansa. Dahil mini-MISLEAD ng LOCAL MEDIA ang buong mundo kaugnay sa totoong nangyayari sa ating bansa. Huwag po tayong maging kampante dahil hindi kampante ang KALABAN ni P.Duterte. TAYO AY NASA ISANG REBOLUSYON LABAN SA OLIGARCHS, DRUG LORDS at mga AMBISYOSONG POLITIKO.  Panoorin ang VIDEO.

STATEMENT BY MAYOR INDAY SARA ON THE FRIDAY NIGHT BLAST IN DAVAO CITY
I would like to express my deepest condolences to the families of those who died last night.
I would also like to reassure all of them, as well as the families of those who are injured that the City Government of Davao will assist in all their needs for hospitalization, burial, funeral and day to day expenses.
I am sorry for what happened.
I would like to remind other officials to stay within the bounds of their official duties according to their position. Please leave me in peace to do my job and I'll leave you to focus on your own work.
We will not be terrorized by this heinous crime and I call on all Dabawenyos to unite and let us help each other rise from this senseless incident.
Let us remain vigilant, please report any and all suspicious activity, no matter how insignificant it may seem.
There will be a memorial at 4:00 this afternoon at the explosion site. Everybody is welcome to say their prayer, lay their flowers and light a candle for those who passed.
Thank you.

Lingid sa kaalaman ng marami, ang Duterte Administration ay abalang abala sa pagpapalaganap ng rehabilitation program para sa mga drug users na sumuko. Mahigit 700,000 drug personalities na ang sumuko sa loob lamang ng isang buwan. Ayon sa PDEA, bukod sa 700k na sumuko ay mayroon pang 2.3M drug users and pushers ang kanilang kailangang tugisin. Ano na ngayon ang mangyayari sa mga sumuko na drug users? Laging binabanggit ni P. Duterte sa kanyang speech na hindi niya inaasahan na ganito na pala kalala ang problema ng droga sa ating bayan. Kaya naman nakikipag ugnayan ang ating gobyerno sa iba't ibang sektor ng ating lipunan upang maging kabahagi ng rehabilitasyon ng mga drug users. Katulad na lamang ng SIPAG "Simula ng Pag-asa". *** Sent thru my email
Hi Mocha,

Isa po akong Licensed Customs Broker but I had stopped practicing my profession dahil hindi ko kaya ang kalakaran sa Bureau of Customs, lahat po kasi umiikot lang sa pera even legitimate naman yung transaction ko. Nakaka-frustrate po kasi pinaghirapan ko po yung course ko para makapagtapos at pati pagpasa sa board exam para maging isang customs broker. Sa umpisa parang ayos lang pero di nagtagal parang may mali na at hindi na kaya ng konsensya ko na magpatuloy. Ang problema po ay yung nakaupo sa pwesto kasi nga naman immune na sila sa kanilang gawain na parang wala ng puso, ang sa kanila lang basta makahawak ng pera ayos na yun, though hindi ko naman nilalahat pero karamihan po sa kanila ganun ang sistema.

Suggestion ko lang po para malinis yung Bureau of Customs, kung hindi kaya ni commisioner alisin ang mga buaya sa customs, ilipat nalang sila sa ibang area, division or port kung saan mapuputol ang kanilang mga illegal trasaction kasi nga naman nakapag-establish na yan sila ng mga kanilang sariling connections at suking ginagatasan. Yung mga official nga ng Bureau may mga kanya-kanya din yang mga importer-clients which is hindi dapat for it is conflict of interest. Pero if ire-reassign sila sa ibang department or port, ofcourse maninibago sila sa kanilang environment at may chance na maputol yung illegal na gawain nila. Every port kasi may mga team na yan sila at naghahati sa perang ninakaw nila sa bayan. Malalakas ang loob at halang ang kaluluwa mga wala naman alam sa Tariff and Customs law kasi iba ang natapos at nakapasok lang sa customs kasi may mga endorsers na politician at nagbayad para lang makapasok sa trabaho.

Another point, maraming hao siao sa bureau na nagtatrabaho sa malalaking opisyal at yung bossing paalis-alis nalang kasi meron ng nagtatrabaho on behalf of them. Nakakalungkot po isipin na hindi masugpo ang corruption despite sa calling ni President Duterte kasi until now ganu parin ang gawain especially sa isang malaking port sa Mindanao. Hindi mapo-process yung papel mo pag hindi ka nagbigay ng pera at parang normal lang sa kanila ni walang bakas na takot.

Gusto ko po mabago yung Bureau para makabalik na ako sa business kasi against talaga ako sa present system nila at hindi ako makabalik kung yung mga nakaupo sa customs mga mukhang pera.

Sana po maipaabot mo kay commisioner kasi minsa na ako nagsuggest at nagreklamo sa hotline ng bureau pero deadma lang sila. 

Hindi man ako magaling magsulat sana po naintindihan mo ang message na nais kong iparating.

Truly yours,

Citizen of the Philippines

There've been lots of Foreigners (non-Filipinos) meddling in the Philippines' internal affairs based on WRONG and INCOMPLETE information that results from the malicious and deliberate misinformation campaign by oligarch-owned anti-reform mass media companies in the Philippines.

To all fellow Filipinos, DO NOT TAKE IT AGAINST THE FOREIGNERS/non-Filipinos who criticize Duterte. They are mostly misinformed and are limited only to the few bits of news in English that is often fed to international news agencies by the same biased oligarch-controlled local Philippine news agencies.

Many Foreigners, particularly Westerners are often open to standing corrected if and when the real facts are presented to them.

It is the oligarch-owned Pinoy Mass Media news outlets that must be condemned for the deliberate unfair and one-sided partisan misrepresentation that they do. The foreigners who criticize Duterte and us Filipinos who voted for him do so based on wrong information that is not of their doing. They are excused since they have no access to information sources in Tagalog, Cebuano or other languages in order for them to verify what needs to be verified. It is our duty TO CORRECT THEM and remind them of the facts that they have not been made aware of by the biased news reports that filtered in to their news sources.

(When many Foreigners find out that Duterte is pushing for constitutional reforms that will lead to a shift to the Federal-Parliamentary System, most of them realize that he's not some power-hungry despot-wannabe, because Federalism is about devolving certain powers (particularly economic development decision-making) away from the Capital and thus lessening micro-managing by the central government which he controls and plus, moving to a Parliamentary System means shifting power over to a COLLEGIAL BODY - the legislature - rather than a unilateral one-man executive regime which is what a presidential system is all about. Such reforms that aim to ultimately lessen the power of the office he currently holds are NOT IN LINE with what power-hungry despots do.)

This video is for FOREIGNERS and Filipinos alike who criticize Duterte because of a lack of knowledge of the full context of Duterte's long years of leadership experience and the context of the Philippines' problems.

BAKIT BA MAHALAGA ANG USAPING PANGKAPAYAPAAN?

Dahil sa tindi ng PROPAGANDA ng mga DILAW sa EXTRAJUDICIAL KILLING,  nakalimutan na natin ang isang magandang nangyayari sa ating gobyerno at eto ay ang pag resume ng PEACE TALK kahapon.
Sabi nga ni P.Duterte kung meron man siyang gustong iwan ay ang KAPAYAPAAN sa pagitan ng mga LEFTIST. Bakit ba mahalaga ito sa ating bayan? 
Dahil tayo ay taga-Manila maaaring hindi natin lubos na nauunawaan ang lalim nito ngunit ang ating Pangulo na laki sa Mindanao ay lubhang naiintindihan niya ito. Dahil ang apektado ng gyera o labanan ay lagi ang inosenteng kababayan natin. At kasabay nito ay ang mga namamatay nating mga sundalo. Sabi nga nila- sa GIYERA walang nanalo kundi may mga NAMAMATAY. Kaya ganoon na lamang ang lubos na pagnanais ng ating Pangulo na magkaroon ng kapayapaan sa ating bansa. Inumpisahan niya ito noong naglagay siya ng mga makakaliwang tao sa kanyang gobyerno. Pangalawa, laging bukas ang Malacanang para sa mga aktibista na ngayon lamang  nangyari sa buong kasaysayan ng ating bansa. Sabi nga ng aking aktibistang kaibigan na si Nato, kitang-kita nila ang puso ng ating Pangulo para sa mga naaapi at mahihirap. At ang aking hiling din sa ating mga ka-DDS na huwag po natin sana husgahan ang mga makakaliwa at alamin ang tunay na dahilan ng kanilang ipinaglalaban. Tulad nga ng sinabi ng ating Pangulo noong panahon ng kampanya na siya ay isang "sosyalista" at siya ay para sa mga ORDINARYONG PILIPINO at HINDI sa mga OLIGARKO. Kaya paulit-ulit din niyang sinasabi na ang kanyang partido ay BAYAN. Panahon na para ibaba ang mga armas at talagang solusyonan na ang problemang dekada ng sumisira sa ating bayan. Naniniwala ako na ang talagang kalaban natin ay ang mga mayayamang elitistang nagpapahirap sa ating mga ordinaryong mamamayan at yan ang tinatawag ni Pangulo na mga OLIGARCH.

Paulit ulit akong tinatanong ng media kung ako daw ba ay magkakaroon ng position sa GOBYERNO at paulit ulit ko din pong sinasabi na wala po akong interes na pumasok sa gobyerno o sa anumang position. Madalas din akong tanungin ng mga reporter kung ano daw ba ang aking reaksyon sa mga "entertainer supporters" ni P.Duterte na na-appoint tulad na lang ni Jimmy Bondoc, Arnel Igancio at ang bagong appointees na si Aiza at Liza. Eto lamang po ang aking masasabi -sa totoo lang sobrang daming magagaling at matatalino sa ating bansa ngunit magtataka ka kung bakit lugmok pa rin tayo sa kahirapan. Sa nakaraang dekada napakarami nating matatalinong mambabatas at gov't officials ngunit bakit tayo pa rin ay isang 3rd world country? Dahil hindi lamang talino ang kailangan natin sa gobyerno ngunit higit sa lahat kailangan natin ng mga tao sa gobyerno na may TUNAY NA PAGMAMAHAL SA ATING BAYAN. DAHIL BIBIHIRA KA MAKAKITA NG MGA SENADOR O KONGRESISTA NA MAY TUNAY NA PAGMAMAHAL SA BAYAN. Yan masakit na katotohonan. Tanggalin mo ang PDAF/DAP/PORK BARREL tignan ko lang kung muling kumandidato ang ilan diyan sa kanila. Our country needs people in the government who really love our nation. At sa tingin ko naman yan ang puso nila Jimmy, Arnel, Liza at Aiza. Dahil noon pa man sila ay nakitaan ko na ng ganyang character. Ako po ay nagagalak dahil tayo ay napaunlakan na makausap at ma-interview si Cabinet Secretary JUN EVASCO. Bigyan ko lamang po kayo ng background kung sino po si Sir JUN. Mahalaga po kasi na makilala natin si Sir Jun dahil siya po ang isa sa pinaka malapit sa ating Pangulo. Si sir Jun Evasco po ay matalik na kaibigan ng ating pangulo. Siya po ay dating PARI na sumanib sa NPA at naging Mayor ng isang town sa Bohol. Magkasama na po sila ni P.Duterte noong prosecutor pa lamang po si PRRD. Si Sir Jun ang naging campaign manager ni P.Duterte noong tumakbo itong Mayor sa Davao. Etong huling eleksyon si Sir Jun ang naging NATIONAL CAMPAIGN MANAGER ni P. Duterte. Ganyan po sila kalapit sa isa't isa. Kaya napakahalagang makilala po natin siya. Isang karangalan ang ma-interview si Cabinet Secretary Jun Evasco sapagka't  siya'y hindi nagpapa-interview sa mainstream media.

MANILA, Philippines ‚Äî While admiring President Duterte's political will in the campaign against drugs, Sen. Leila de Lima on Sunday emphasized the need for evidence and due process in bringing drug suspects to justice, or else the public revelation of their names may be regarded as no less than a "witch hunt."
Sought for comment, De Lima, chair of the Senate committee on justice and human rights, said the latest names aired by Duterte in a speech early Sunday should be pursued in court if there was evidence, as the law dictated.
"To be honest, it's difficult to pass judgment on the style of the President, especially that a great majority of our people seem to approve of this naming and shaming strategy," De Lima told the Inquirer when reached yesterday.

She added, "If the President thinks it's an effective strategy, then who are we to dictate on him. His strong will and great determination to end the drug problem deserve high praise and credit."
"Having said that, as a student of constitutional law, let me express these thoughts: If there is evidence against these people he has named and shamed, cases should just be filed against them so that warrants for their arrest can be issued. If there is no evidence, then this is a plain and simple witch hunt," she said.
The lawmaker, who recently appealed for an end to the string of deaths of suspected criminals, warned that being publicly named as a drug suspect was "already a death sentence," given the President's standing "shoot-to-kill" order on narco-politicians who would resist arrest.
"We are already in the slippery slope towards tyranny, without martial law, when we allow one man to be judge, jury and executioner. This is just the start," De Lima said.
"The end game is just too terrible to imagine, when anyone can be accused and shot on sight based on a list that has the same legal value as a grocery list," she said.
De Lima is set to conduct a legislative inquiry on the spate of killings of drug suspects in police operations and vigilante-style executions amid Duterte's drug war./rga

Duterte si Sir FAELDON bilang commissioner ng BOC, ako po ay natuwa ng sobra. Nakasama po namin siya noong panahon ng Campaign. Eto po yung huling bahagi ng campaign kung saan si TRILLANES ay PURO KASINUNGALINGAN ang ibinabato sa ating Pangulo. Si FAELDON ang nagmulat sa tao na si TRILLANES ay TRAYDOR sa kanilang PRINSIPYO at SAMAHAN. Sobrang taas ang tingin ko kay sir FAELDON kaya't  hindi ko maitugma na umabot na ng isang buwan sa BOC ay marami pa rin ang nagsasabing wala o kaunti pa lamang ang nagbabago sa BOC. Kaya talagang pilit ko siyang hinagilap at nagpa-set ng appointment upang klaruhin ito para na rin sa mga ka-DDS natin na nag aantay ng pagbabago sa BOC. Ikinuwento po sa akin ni Sir Faeldon (off the record) kung bakit kakaunti pa ang nagbabago sa BOC. Isa na dito ay lahat ng parte ng BOC ay CORRUPT o di kaya'y ayaw naman magsumbong. Pinaliwanag niya sa akin na hindi siya basta-basta maaring magtanggal ng mga officials ng walang SAPAT na ebidensya. At karamihan ng mga tao ay nasanay na sa bulok na pamamalakad sa CUSTOMS. Sa madaling salita, sila-sila ay magkakakuntsaba kaya walang nakakasuhan. TANDAAN PO NATIN, sa mata ng BATAS pag walang sapat ng EBIDENSYA ito ay tsismis lamang. Dahil dito walang nahuhuling tiwaling traffic enforcer. Tandaan, barya lamang po yan kumpara sa TAX ng binabayaran ng mga importers o di kaya freight forwarders. Usapan dito ay DAANG DAANG LIBO at MILYUN MILYON. Nag-iisa pa lamang si SIR FAELDON na appointed ng ating Pangulo sa BOC. Inaayos pa na maipasok ang mga tiwalang tauhan ni Comm. Faeldon. Kaya nga po ang kanyang panawagan sa mga mamamayang Pilipino ay kung may alam kayong corruption (detelyado, handa kang sumumpa at maging testigo) ay mag reklamo ng direkta sa opisina ni Sir Faeldon at kayo ay kanyang haharapin. Zamboanga lawmaker opposes mandatory drug tests for Congress

Metro Manila (CNN Philippines) ‚Äî With the Duterte administration's strong anti-drugs campaign, one lawmaker wants mandatory drug testing for all members of Congress and their staff.

But another lawmaker is opposing it.

"Mandatory drug test for all just to address a few cases is unnecessary," said Gloria Labadlabad, Zambaonga Del Norte 2nd District Representative.

Labadlabad is contesting the resolution filed by Surigao Del Norte Representative Robert Ace Barbers that aims for a drug-free Congress.

According to a statement, Labadlabad said "there is no need for lawmakers to undergo such drug test personally because of her high regard in the integrity of the majority of the elected legislators."

Barbers' resolution requires all lawmakers, their staff, consultants, officers, and all employees of the House to take periodic drug tests.

Those who fail to comply will face sanctions and will not receive their salaries and benefits.

"The House of Representatives should underscore its commitment, support and participation to anti-drug policies, programs and projects by ensuring that its own workplace is a drug-free institution," Barbers said.

Malaca√±ang recently said it is in favor of mandatory drug testing for all government employees.

Presidential Spokesperson Ernesto Abella said drug tests would show if people in government are "worthy of trust."

Mga pagbabago sa Dept. Of Transportation (DOT)

Noong July 15 ng hapon ako po ay nagtungo sa DOT (dating DOTC dahil ihihiwalay na daw ang Communications) upang iparating ang inyong mga hinaing kay SEC. Arthur "Art" Tugade. Unfortunately, nagkaroon po ng problema ang aking microphone kung kaya't hindi na-record ang unang bahagi ng interview. Pinag-usapan doon ang problema sa airport katulad ng "laglag bala", pangingikil at panga-abuso ng ilang mga opisyal ng airport. Iginiit ni Sec. Art Tugade na siya ay galit na galit sa pangingikil kung kaya't magkakaroon ng 24-hour complaint desk sa tanggapan ng DOT kung saan pwede magreklamo. Binanggit din niya ang kanyang personal email address ngunit hindi ito nasagap ng microphone. Aalamin ko po sa lalong madaling panahon ang kanyang email ad at ipo-post ko po dito.  At sa mga nabiktima ng  "laglag bala", hindi na kayo pwedeng hulihin o ikulong. Ang gagawin lamang ninyo ay i-surrender ang bala. 
Pinakinggan din ni Sec. Tugade ang inyong mga suhestiyon para ma-resolba ang problema sa trapiko. Pinag-usapan din po ang mga mapang-abusong taxi drivers at ang matagal na pagrelease ng driver's license/plate numbers.

Pagkatapos ng interview, tayo po ay napaunlakan na makasama at makita ang presentation ng Urban Cable Car System na isa sa mga paraan upang mabigyan ng kaginhawaan ang ating mga commuters. Ito ay hango sa makabagong sistema ng transportasyon sa bansang Bolivia. Ang Phase 1 ay magmumula sa Tutuban papuntang Ortigas Center. Aabutin lamang ng 18 to 24 months ang construction ng Phase 1. Plano din lagyan ng cable car system mula La Union papuntang Baguio City. Isa lang po ito sa mga solusyon sa trapiko. Marami pa pong magagandang proyekto ang nakalaan ngunit maisasakatuparan lamang ang mga ito kung mabibigyan ng "Special Powers" ng Kongreso si Sec. Tugade. Higit sa lahat, walang ilalabas na pera ang Gobyerno sa pagpapatupad nito kung kaya't siguradong walang korupsyon. Pang-siyam (9) na araw pa lamang ni Sec. Tugade sa kanyang tungkulin noong siya'y aking na-interview ngunit mabilis siyang nagtatrabaho at marami ng nagagawa. Ibinulong niya sa akin na marami na rin siyang tinanggal na mga tiwaling opisyal ng DOT o Dept. of Transportation.
Political will... Yan ang wala sa nakaraang administrasyon.

REPOST FROM SEC. MANNY PINOL

President Ordinary

JUST CALL ME RODY,
NOT 'YOUR EXCELLENCY'

By Manny Pi√±ol

A funny thing happened Monday night when I made a presentation before the Cabinet the planned preparation for the expected onslaught of La Ni√±a, the climatic phenomenon which brings unusually heavy rains.

Following protocol, I started my presentation with the usual courtesies for President Rody Duterte and the members of the Cabinet.

"You Excellency, members of the Cabinet ...," I saif as I began to explain why, in the face of the unpredictability of climate, the country must strive to attain not only rice self-sufficiency but establish a 6-month buffer stock.

Halfway through my presentation and as I kept repeating "Your Excellency" to address President Duterte, I noticed that he pulled a piece of paper and a ballpen from Finance Secretary Sonny Dominguez.

Sec. Dominguez sits between me and the President.

After scribbling something on the piece of paper, President Duterte pushed it to Sec. Dominguez who passed it on to me.

Pausing from my presentation to read the Presidential note, I read the message:

"Stop addressing me Your Excellency. Just call me Rody," the note from the President said.

I chuckled and told him: "Sorry, Mr. President."

While he simply wanted me and the other members of the Cabinet to call him "Rody," protocol dictates that we address him using his title "Mr. President."

This is how simple this President is. 

This is the President who told airport authorities not to suspend commercial flights whenever he uses the airport.

This is the President who has instructed his Cabinet members to travel economy class and to use ordinary vehicles without the No. 6 plate reserved for Department Secretaries.

He leads by example in living a simple lifestyle.

President Duterte is President Ordinary.

REPOST FROM 
HACIENDA LUISITA PAGE
Bernardina L. Bais, 66 years old, mourns the death of her palay crops sprayed with non selective herbicide, gramoxole, that kills weeds but also includes all other green plants. These were sprayed by paid personnels of the Cojuangco-Aquino.

This is not a farmer vs. farmer dispute. This is an orchestrated chaos architecturally designed by the Cojuangco-Aquino to hide their involvement. But which administration implemented the divisive tambiolo distribution-a distribution that paved the way for farmers towards selling or renting out their stake on lands they were allocated that are too far from their residential homes. Why does Dina Catalan continues to plant in their decades long planting ground when they themselves have lot allotments in brgy. Motrico? But Motrico is 8 km away, located in the municipality of La Paz while they had been living their lives in Tarlac City. And why does the farmers of brgy. Texas thrown from their own planting grounds 3 km away to the neighboring Brgy. Mapalacsiao? Because their own planting grounds, hundreds of hectares of fertile and agricultural in nature and in use, were illegally converted and made exempted from land distribution.

And, can an ordinary farmer, just wanting to plant their own crops can really have the gall to destroy and purposely kill the food crops of his fellow farmer? Can he even spare 3,000 php for a gramoxole sprayer kit when 3,000 php is already a large sum for most farmworkers? Can he have 9 large tractors to command and diesel to support the machine and even can he pay the operator driving it if he is but a mere farmworker?

Why is there the presence of Buena Timbol, and Villamor Lagunero, known to have publicly represented various companies ubder the Jose Cojuangco and Sons group of companies?

Can a farmer who have not sold nor rented out his land really choose to destroy a rice plant to plant sugarcanes? (Around 20 hectares of land that were destroyed last July 1 were simultaneously being planted with sugarcanes!)

Is it really the farmers of Texas just wanting their piece of land? 

We do not condemn our fellow farmers frailties but we condemn those who take advantage of their plights and poverty and those who have the gall to use our own class against their own. We condemn the continued unceasing impunity and terror that these land lord - large bourgeois comprador - bureaucrat capitalist Cojuangco - Aquino family place upon our people! 

We demand justice! We demand our land!

Kaya naiinis ang mga tao sa mga Media dahil sa mga ganito. Kala ko ba wala kayong kinikilingan? 

*** OPEN LETTER OF BRUCE RIVERA TO RAFFY TIMA 
Dear Mr. Tima,
Yes, we get it. You are still angry because of the "catcalling" issue but is it really necessary to do this? PNoy said no to wang-wang but there was no serious threat to his life. Even his haters do not want to kill him.
But this time, our President is fighting a war that has all the means to fight back and kill him. He knows the threat to his life and he knows that some of the people presently kissing his ass are the very one out to destroy him. He knows very well that his enemies will go to the extent of destroying even his avid supporters to discredit him and everything he stands for.
So cut him some slack and leave the Filipino in peace not to worry about the safety of our President because a journalist is complaining about traffic in EDSA as if it was a rare occurrence. In fact, our President did not claim to fix the EDSA traffic in his term. He knows it is impossible. So quit on the nitpicking and just understand that we want our President alive to make good his promise.
Because in reality, I am used to the traffic in EDSA. That is why I avoid it. But I would rather worry about traffic than worry whether I am going to be alive if ever I traverse that road.
We ask but a little understanding.
Thank you.

FROM RENATO REYES 
Secretary General at Bagong Alyansang Makabayan (BAYAN)

Two reporters asked me if I wore jeans inside Malacanang. I did not immediately see the relevance of the question. Then they explained that jeans weren't allowed in Malacanang. Really? We didn't know. Well, it didn't seem to be a big deal to the new occupants. The President by the way wore corduroy pants when he met with us. So, yeah.

*** Today, leaders of Bayan met with President Rodrigo Duterte at the Osmena Room in Malacanang to congratulate him on his inauguration and to submit to him the People's Agenda for Change which was drafted by the National People's Summit. We were fetched by the PSG as the Mendiola rally was still ongoing. There were no costume changes. We were in typical sweaty rally attire when we entered Malacanang, passing by the departing Palace guests who were dressed in their best formal wear.
We were warmly received at the Osmena Room. Our delegation consisted of myself for BAYAN, Elmer Labog for KMU, Sarah Elago for Kabataan, Cristina Palabay of Karapatan, Christian Tuayon of Bayan Negros, Windel Bolinget from Cordillera People's Alliance, Diego Torres from Bayan Southern Tagalog, Eufemia Cullamat, Lumad from CARAGA, Liza Maza of P1NAS and Makabayan, and Antonio Flores of KMP.
We discussed a wide range of issues including contractualization, destructive mining, ancestral lands, land reform, the release of political prisoners on humanitarian grounds, increasing the budget for health services and education. He sympathized with the release of political prisoners on humanitarian grounds since he had seen similar cases in Davao before. He is studying the possibility of distributing 6 million hectares of public land to farmers. He is a firm believer of the principle of land to the tiller. He wants a review of existing laws on ancestral lands.
He asked us if this was our first time inside Malacanang. For most, it was. We told him how we are usually barred from crossing the barricades at Mendiola. He told us that he respects freedom of speech and the right to peaceably assemble. I asked him if this meant that we can hold our SONA rally closer to Batasan. He said it shouldn't be a problem. Pwede raw makalapit.
He wants peace and national unity to be his legacy. He is serious about finding a solution to the armed conflict.
When it was time to present our tokens, he gamely posed for pictures. He was the first to raise his fist, and we followed his lead. I told him that we don't remember any sitting president raising his fist like that. He said it was because he was serious in his pledge of bringing change. We wished him good luck and thanked him for receiving us on his inauguration day. The meeting lasted for 40 minutes.
P.S.
The last time I set foot in Malacanang was in 2001, right after EDSA 2 and just before EDSA 3. That was 15 years ago.

PARA SA MEDIA AT MGA JOURNALISTS

Hindi ko maintindihan kung bakit nag-iinit ang pwet ninyo. Instead of understanding the revelation of President Duterte on the corruption of these media people you focus on my qualification as a Journalist?
Paulit-ulit ko naman sinabi na hindi ako journalist. Hindi ako nag-aral ng journalism. At huwag kayong mag-alala hindi ko rin sinabi na higit ako sa inyo dahil kayo'y matalino, professional at magaling. Ngunit isa lang ang maipagmamalaki ko - HINDI AKO BAYARAN. And you missed the whole point of the video which is the corruption in your profession. Na-miss ninyo ba o sadyang tinamaan lang kayo? Buti nalang talaga hindi nanalo yang kandidato ninyo kung hindi mas lalo pang lalala ang corruption sa inyong hanay. 
Uulitin ko ha, HINDI AKO JOURNALIST. At wala akong pangarap maging Journalist. I am just doing this to serve my fellow ordinary Filipino people who are asking me for help. Kayo, why are you doing your job?
Goodbye Mr. Aquino

DOJ RESOLUTIONS FOR SALE AT 3MILLION ???

"We are calling for the DOJ and incoming President Rodrigo Duterte na tutukan ang mga issue ng 'resolutions for sale' at 'midnight resolutions.' Gusto lang namin na silipin lahat ng transparency sa mga kaso sa DOJ," FATE spokesperson Jo Perez told GMA News Online.
Perez said based on information gathered by their team, Caparas had instructed DOJ undersecretaries and prosecutors to stop issuing decisions by June 3 and go on forced leaves so he could rewrite them himself.
She alleged that the rewritten rulings were being "antedated" and being sold for "millions of pesos," which she termed as "padulas" or "grease money."
"Amusing" accusation
Caparas, who is about to vacate his post when President Benigno Aquino III steps down from office on June 30, quickly dismissed the accusation, calling it "amusing."
advertisement

"What they claim is all untrue. No 'meddling' and 'midnight reversals' (whatever that means) and no instruction from me or my office to anyone in DOJ to take 'forced leaves,'" Caparas told GMA News Online in a text message.
The Justice secretary added: "I can only wonder who is or are behind FATE."
Caparas said "personal interest" could be the motive behind such accusations.
Money-related?
According to Perez, they learned that Caparas had been "scrambling" to rewrite decisions just weeks before Duterte is set to ascend to the highest post in the land.
Perez said their group "cannot divulge at this time" where and how they got the information about the alleged "midnight reversals," as she urged the government to conduct further investigation on the controversy.
She said rulings on both high-profile and regular cases were affected by the alleged "midnight reversals."
More than politics, Perez suspected that the midnight resolutions could be "much more money-related." "Kung kailan siya bababa sa posisyon, ito ang time na nangyayari ang resolution for sale. Baka iniisip nila dito makalusot ang kaso," she said. ‚ÄîKBK, GMA News

NBI: Whatever killed partygoers blew up their heart, organs

Whatever Bianca Fontejon, and Lance Garcia ingested during Saturday's outdoor concert at the SM Mall of Asia, it had the same effect as swallowing an explosive.
"There was bleeding in the internal organs which is highly unusual in cases like these. Almost all internal organs were involved‚Äîthe brain, the lungs,  the liver, the intestines, the spleen and the kidneys," National Bureau of Investigation medico legal officer Wilfredo Tierra told the Inquirer on Wednesday.
Whatever it was that they took, it was potent enough to damage all of their internal organs which carried signs of ruptured tissues or blood vessels, he said.

But what struck him the most, Tierra added, was the state of the victims' hearts‚Äîboth looked as if they had been grilled as these were a mixture of brown, red and black in color.
"It was the first time I had ever seen something like this," said the medico legal officer who has been performing autopsies for 20 years.
He added: "This is a severe form, [at] the extreme [end] of the spectrum of a heart attack because during the conduct of the autopsy, almost all parts of the heart were involved."
Tierra, who autopsied the victims' bodies, earlier said that Fontejon, who was only 18 years old; and Garcia, aged 36; had died of a heart attack.
He clarified, however, on Wednesday that the two did not die solely of a heart attack, saying their deaths were unusual because all their internal organs failed.
According to Tierra, there was bleeding and swelling in the victims' brains and large intestines while there were also signs of hemorrhage in a big portion of their lungs.
"We will take this as a whole. Heart attack was not the only cause of death. If what was taken was ingested, the whole body system was affected," he said.
Tierra went on to say that based on the condition of their hearts, it was also the first time that the victims had suffered a heart attack. A "normal heart attack" would only change the organ's color from pink to slight brown, not black like the victims'.

However, he declined to speculate on what had caused the bleeding, saying the NBI's forensic division was still finalizing the report on the results of the toxicology and dangerous drugs tests.
Fontejon and Garcia were among five people who suddenly collapsed at the Closeup Forever Summer outdoor concert. All died hours later in the hospital. The autopsies conducted on two other victims, Eric Anthony Miller and Ken Migawa, showed that they suffered sudden cardiac death.

People ask me kung meron daw ba akong hihingin kapalit kay Duterte. Kung meron man pagkakataon na makahingi ako ng something kay Duterte, hihingin ko na makulong ang mga politikong taksil sa bayan sa nakaraang gobyerno tulad ni Aquino, Abad, Trillanes, Roxas, Binay at lalong lalo na ang head ng NAIA na nagpahirap sa mga OFW natin.

Some said they missed the part kung saan yung "What MG had to give up?"

Ganito lang yan. Alam naman natin DUTERTE's TEAM has no budget. When we started to verbally support DUTERTE ay big risk for my group. LP has the most money. We have invitations on different provinces to perform on LGU candidates under LP. We decline even malaki ang kita dito. Anything to do with other candidates we decline. We only campaign and perform for DUTERTE kahit walang bayad. And now alam na ng lahat that we are supporters of Duterte syempre any shows that are sponsored by a mayor in province not with Duterte hindi na kami kukunin. Malaki po yan dahil madami ang fiesta sa Pilipinas. Dyan kumikita ang mga tulad naming entertainers. Yan po yun ibig sabihin ng WHAT WE HAD TO GIVE UP sa article. Marami sa mga entertainers ay DUTERTE talaga but they didnt support him all out kasi it will affect their business. I am not saying this to glorify my group. We did this kasi nga yung nga mga kababayan natin na wala ng makain eh gumagastos para ma campaign lang si DUTERTE eh kami tf lang mawawala. Logic lang po yun. Nakakakonsyensa naman na ang mga kababayan natin naghihirap para makampanya si Duterte tayong mga artist gusto pa kumita sa kampanya? Kapal naman ng muka natin kung ganun. I dont even consider ourselves doing much for our country. Kulang pa po ang aming ginawa kumpara sa inyo lalo na sa mga OFW na todo talaga ang suporta at matinding sakripisyo ang ginawa upang ikampanya si Duterte. 

Asahan nyo pa po na ang blog ko ay inyong boses. my group is not affiliated in anyway sa kahit sinong politiko not even to PDP LABAN or to DUTERTE. Ako po ay para sa bayan at sa mga ordinaryong Pilipino na nangangailangan ng boses. At sa pagkakataon na ito si DUTERTE ang sigaw ng ordinaryong PILIPINO. At ulitin ko hindi ako tatakbo sa Politika dahil naniniwala ako hindi mo kailangan nasa gobyerno upang makatulong  sa iyong kapwa.
